<font color="#FF0000">USAF PJ EQUIPMENT  </font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep 27 17:19:00 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
We had a lot of very specialized gear to jump with, including:<br><br>
--Tree suits (like the smokejumpers wear) for land/tree jumps.<br>
--Para-scuba jumps, wearing wet suits, fins, mask (behind our neck), scuba tank &amp; regulator, reserve and main 'chute, medical kit (35 lbs) and a butt boat (one-man life raft with survival gear).  <br><br>
We also had gear dropped to us if necessary.<br><br>
None of this was used in 'Nam.  We used helicopters and their hoists as delivery platforms for the rescue work.  Our mission was rescue behind enemy lines, North Vietnam, Loas and Combodia.  For these rescues, we descended the hoist with the medical kit and radio (tied into our headset) for communication.  
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


